&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Dental Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference No: J127-A-20-0615&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: Full time, 37.5 hours &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bases: Meadows Health Centre, 1 Bridgeway Centre, Meadows, Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, NG2 2JG&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £21,892 – £24,157 per annum &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to make a real difference in a socially minded, values driven organisation?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to work where your voice can be heard?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are an award winning employee owned social enterprise, providing high quality community dental services across east and central England.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you ever pictured yourself working in a dental clinic with a highly experienced and specialised team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your answer is ‘yes’ and you see yourself as a caring, compassionate, flexible and approachable person where you will be appreciated by patients and the team, then this is the place for you. Your good communication skills and effortless ways of making people feel at ease will come in really handy when providing valuable support at these clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your primary responsibility will be to provide clinical support in a wide range of treatments for a broad client base which includes adults and children, patients with additional needs, phobics and the elderly. Extended duties would be a distinct advantage. We would like you to have a welcoming and positive approach for our patients and be an upbeat and reliable member of the team. Our clinical sessions run between Monday to Friday 8:30 am to 6:00 pm. We will need you to be flexible in your approach to work and on occasion we will need you to work at other clinics across Nottinghamshire, so car drivers are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full time, 5 days, 37.5 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Starting salary gross £21,892 per annum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurturing and caring work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information about the role, please contact Amanda Stevenson, Senior Dental Nurse 07775 031916.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are happy to go straight ahead with an application, please apply online at NHS Jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;strong&gt; 06th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 17th / 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Head Office: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Community Dental Services CIC, Colworth House, Colworth Park, Sharnbrook, Bedfordshire,&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;MK44 1LZ Tel no: 0333 207 5992&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
